tafsir[5]{c,v,t}:
  109,2,"I do not and will not worship the idols you worship."
  109,4,"Nor am I going to worship the idols you worship."
  110,2,"And you see the people entering into Islam in delegations upon delegations."
  111,1,"Both hands of the uncle of the Prophet (peace be upon him): Abū Lahab son of ‘Abdul Muṭṭalib have lost because of the loss of his actions; he used to harm the Prophet (peace be upon him). His efforts are in vain."
  111,5,"Around her neck will be tightly bound a rope with which she will be dragged into the hellfire."